You are implementing WP-NEXT-47 in the BIM AI web app (`/Users/jhoetter/repos/bim-ai`). The task is to improve the contextual Modify tab in section and sheet views to show real modify verbs instead of the current "Select-only" stub.

## Background

`packages/web/src/workspace/shell/RibbonBar.tsx` builds ribbon tabs per view mode. The functions that need changing:

1. `buildSectionRibbonTabs` (line 1414) — when `selectedElementKind` is truthy, currently calls `buildSelectionOnlyModifyTab(selectedElementKind)`. This should instead call a new `buildSectionModifyTab(selectedElementKind)`.

2. `buildSheetRibbonTabs` (line 1460) — similarly uses `buildSelectionOnlyModifyTab`. Should use a new `buildSheetModifyTab(selectedElementKind)`.

3. `buildScheduleRibbonTabs` (line 1524) — uses `buildSelectionOnlyModifyTab`. In schedule view, all modify verbs are disabled (per the `getModifyAvailability` spec), so the modify tab should NOT be added at all. Remove the `if (selectedElementKind)` block entirely from `buildScheduleRibbonTabs`.

## What to implement

Add these two new functions **immediately before** `buildSelectionOnlyModifyTab` (around line 1669):

```typescript
function buildSectionModifyTab(selectedElementKind: string): RibbonTab {
  return {
    id: 'modify',
    label: `Modify | ${formatKind(selectedElementKind)}`,
    contextual: true,
    panels: [
      {
        id: 'selection',
        label: 'Selection',
        commands: [
          tool('select', 'Select', 'select'),
          tool('move', 'Move', 'move'),
          tool('copy', 'Copy', 'copy'),
          tool('rotate', 'Rotate', 'rotate'),
        ],
      },
      {
        id: 'visibility',
        label: 'Visibility',
        commands: [
          tool('pin', 'Pin', 'pin'),
          tool('unpin', 'Unpin', 'pin'),
        ],
      },
    ],
  };
}

function buildSheetModifyTab(selectedElementKind: string): RibbonTab {
  return {
    id: 'modify',
    label: `Modify | ${formatKind(selectedElementKind)}`,
    contextual: true,
    panels: [
      {
        id: 'selection',
        label: 'Selection',
        commands: [
          tool('select', 'Select', 'select'),
          tool('move', 'Move', 'move'),
          tool('copy', 'Copy', 'copy'),
        ],
      },
      {
        id: 'transform',
        label: 'Transform',
        commands: [
          tool('scale', 'Scale', 'scale'),
        ],
      },
    ],
  };
}
```

## Wire them in

In `buildSectionRibbonTabs`, change:
```typescript
  if (selectedElementKind) {
    tabs.push(buildSelectionOnlyModifyTab(selectedElementKind));
  }
```
to:
```typescript
  if (selectedElementKind) {
    tabs.push(buildSectionModifyTab(selectedElementKind));
  }
```

In `buildSheetRibbonTabs`, change `buildSelectionOnlyModifyTab` to `buildSheetModifyTab`.

In `buildScheduleRibbonTabs`, remove the entire `if (selectedElementKind) { ... }` block (schedule has no enabled modify verbs).

## Check that `pin`, `unpin`, `scale` are valid ToolIds

Before writing, grep the `ToolId` union in `packages/web/src/tools/toolRegistry.ts` to confirm `pin`, `unpin`, and `scale` are in the union. If any are missing, omit them silently (don't add them to the registry — that's out of scope).

## Tests

Check if `packages/web/src/workspace/shell/RibbonBar.test.tsx` exists. If so, add tests for `getRibbonCommandsForMode('section', selectedElementKind)` returning move/copy/rotate and `getRibbonCommandsForMode('schedule', selectedElementKind)` not returning any modify verbs.

## After editing

Run: `pnpm --filter @bim-ai/web typecheck` and `pnpm --filter @bim-ai/web test run -- src/workspace/shell/RibbonBar.test.tsx` (if the test file exists) to confirm no regressions.

Then commit with message: `feat(WP-NEXT-47): section/sheet modify tabs with real verbs; schedule drops modify tab`

Do NOT modify any other files. Do NOT update the tracker — that will be done separately.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 &lt;noreply@anthropic.com&gt;

